{
  "stem": "4513.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And we have a relationship to this day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We both went to Purdue together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "His family was-- was much better off, economically, than my family was, and they lived up the street from us and lived in a very nice house and all this sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we just became good friends, and my mother said a friendship is my protector.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was the protector of him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So-- But it was an all-black school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "All the teachers were black.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And interesting enough, Indianapolis was a very unusual place, because Indianapolis had integrated schools.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was the black community that asked for segregated schools.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the reason why they wanted their schools to be all-black is they wanted a place where they-- where the people who they were getting-- who were going to college could come back and teach in the schools.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So our teachers were black.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Our principals were black.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Even our superintendent-- deputy superintendent was black.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So all of the-- all of our education that we saw was all black folk, all the way through high school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my father worked at several things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, when he came out the army, they trained him to be a tailor.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I  don't think my father was ever the best tailor in the world, but he had a little shop for a while.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When he first came to Indianapolis, while he was recuperating from his tuberculosis, he had a little tailor shop.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, my mother always felt that that was the wrong place because she felt that lint from the clothing would exacerbate his tuberculosis.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- and then finally, he got sick doing it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he did that.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
